subSubSection.paragraph:
Compared with 

Acrotritia dikra
(

Niedbała & Schatz, 
1996

)

, this new species differs by the following features: 
1
) surface of body distinctly foveolate (versus punctate in 

A. dikra

); 
2
) sensilla with flat and truncate head (versus setiform); 
3
) one pair of genital setae in progenital position (versus two pairs).
